## Service Feedback
[Capture ALL feedback mentioned about existing services or tools. Organize by provider/service.]

### AWS Services
[Any feedback, issues, or discussions about AWS services (EC2, S3, Lambda, EKS, SageMaker, Bedrock, Control Tower, Security Hub, IAM, etc.). Include positive feedback, complaints, feature requests, and usage challenges. If no AWS services were discussed, write "Not discussed".]

### NetApp Services
[Any feedback, issues, or discussions about NetApp services (ONTAP, Cloud Volumes, StorageGRID, BlueXP, Astra, etc.). Include positive feedback, complaints, feature requests, and usage challenges. If no NetApp services were discussed, write "Not discussed".]

### Other Services & Tools
[Feedback on any other services, tools, or platforms discussed (e.g., Jira, Confluence, Slack, GitHub, CI/CD pipelines, internal tools). If none discussed, write "Not discussed".]

## Blockers
[Identify ALL blockers mentioned in the meeting. Categorize each blocker into exactly one of these types:]

### Operational Blockers
[Issues related to day-to-day operations: system outages, access problems, tooling failures, deployment issues, on-call burden, incident response gaps. If none, write "None identified".]

### Organizational Blockers
[Issues related to people, teams, processes: unclear ownership, cross-team dependencies, approval bottlenecks, communication gaps, staffing shortages, unclear priorities. If none, write "None identified".]

### Physical / Infrastructure Blockers
[Issues related to hardware, network, data centers, physical equipment, office/remote setup, connectivity. If none, write "None identified".]

### Roadmap / Strategic Blockers
[Issues related to product direction, feature prioritization, technical debt, architecture decisions, migration timelines, vendor decisions. If none, write "None identified".]

